Cell[TextData[{
 "2,000 dimensions suffice for a robot with 100 degrees of freedom and 20 \
actuators, if one seeks the LQR ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["K", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "8b7f101c-dd1d-4dab-9a41-d0585e8182ee"],
 " matrix (see \
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Linear%E2%80%93quadratic_regulator). The ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["K", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "9465a0ad-5453-4645-8935-290411e1947f"],
 " matrix linearly transforms state delta to actuator forces. State delta is \
the difference between current state (simulated or real) and desired state, \
measuring by how much we \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]miss the mark.\
\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] "
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.775402639959318*^9, 3.77540299308497*^9}, {
