Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Problem Statement", "Chapter",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.776078681043211*^9, 
  3.776078685030957*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"20556abe-6b75-4319-b374-\
12c448cc9d9f"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Estimate ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["N", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "f5384d56-51d5-4b46-959e-99a5d94698a6"],
 ", the number of binary judgments needed to find a local maximum of some \
real-valued benefit function. The search depends on a hyperparameter ",
 StyleBox["decay,",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " \[CapitalDelta], explained below. We cannot find ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["N", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "e6611620-0605-4f17-8ee6-3952f21ff44d"],
 " without specifying \[CapitalDelta] and vice versa. ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["N", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "adc32f03-e666-4434-9fd6-0c9fe93e5d23"],
 " and \[CapitalDelta] are linked in a way we do not fully understand. \
However, we can, in practice, find good, paired values of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["N", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "769f7688-3b61-49d5-a71d-667b7a3309e1"],
 " and \[CapitalDelta] such that searches succeed most or even all of the \
time. "
}], "Text",
