Cell[TextData[{
 "The benefit function studied in this notebook is convex, i.e., there is \
only one maximum. Real-world benefit functions may have more than one \
acceptable local maximum. Therefore, the estimated ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["N", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "d006486a-47d1-49ae-8689-de91c4b8fe5e"],
 "s in this notebook are conservative. Real-world counts could be many fewer \
if searches are allowed to find any acceptable local maximum."
}], "Text",
