Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["How a Trial Dies or Wanders", "Section",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.775417581017716*^9, 3.7754175916455936`*^9}, {
  3.775418566239739*^9, 3.775418569889133*^9}, {3.7761069848203382`*^9, 
  3.77610699464468*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"814c5c3d-ea90-456b-bf64-\
ee03807b37e0"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Dying: \[CapitalDelta] too Small", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.775562140943836*^9, 
  3.775562168664403*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"240e8c1f-054c-4ba4-8b28-\
201fa199d066"],

Cell["\<\
When \[CapitalDelta] is too small, with fewer nines, closer to 0 than to 1, \
the search radius shrinks too quickly The trial runs out of gas on a falsely \
positive trail before it gets close to the target. We can guess, ahead of \
time, that it will run out of gas, and we can cut the trial off early (\"We \
might be going in the right direction, but we don\[CloseCurlyQuote]t have \
enough gas to find out.\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]). The point of quitting early \
is to save wall-clock time. Episodes take hours to run and anything that \
speeds them up is worth the trouble. \
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.775402639959318*^9, 3.77540299308497*^9}, {
   3.775403629670733*^9, 3.7754039336643057`*^9}, 3.77540425108463*^9, {
   3.775404295115981*^9, 3.77540431990447*^9}, {3.7754044944105167`*^9, 
   3.775404527060396*^9}, {3.775404669604767*^9, 3.775405029321094*^9}, {
   3.775408740633996*^9, 3.775409121677979*^9}, {3.775409639907167*^9, 
   3.775409678302533*^9}, {3.775409717875424*^9, 3.775409747511722*^9}, {
