   3.911813009934071*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"b50c9bd3-57c3-4d42-b1f5-\
3d951504d9cf"],

Cell["\<\
However, we have a way to find out whether this heuristic is too aggressive, \
i.e., kills the trial too early: run some trials with the death-predictor off \
and compare them to trials with the death-predictor on. If the heuristic is \
too aggressive, then the success rate will be higher with the predictor off. \
We call this test process \"assessing the death tax\" in a section below.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.775402639959318*^9, 3.77540299308497*^9}, {
   3.775403629670733*^9, 3.7754039336643057`*^9}, 3.77540425108463*^9, {
